info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 13 at 2:28AM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Spirit River near Spirit Falls affecting Lincoln County. ...FLOOD WARNING FOR SNOWMELT IN EFFECT FROM EARLY THIS MORNING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Spirit River near Spirit Falls. * WHEN...From early this morning until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 8.0 feet, Floodwaters begin to flow over low spots on Highway T in the Spirit Falls region. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1:30 AM CDT Thursday the stage was 8.1 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 1:30 AM CDT Thursday was 8.1 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 8.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued this afternoon.
